NOTES
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- The HighGrid core library (src/) contains NO bundled third-party code.
  All source code in src/ is original work licensed under MIT.

- sparklinePlugin (src/plugins/sparklinePlugin.js) renders mini charts using
  native browser SVG APIs only. No external charting library is required or
  bundled.

- echartsPlugin (src/plugins/echartsPlugin.js) optionally lazy-loads Apache
  ECharts (entry #2 above) via dynamic import. ECharts is Apache-2.0, which
  is compatible with MIT for use in open-source and commercial projects.

- MIT and Apache-2.0 are both permissive licenses. You can use MIT-licensed
  HighGrid together with Apache-2.0 ECharts without license conflicts.
  However, when distributing a compiled application that includes ECharts,
